         <abstract>
            <p>The problem of simultaneous Chebyshev approximation of a set F of uniformly bounded, real-valued functions on a compact interval I by a set P of continuous functions is equivalent to the problem of simultaneous approximation of two real-valued functions F&lt;sup&gt;+(&lt;/sup&gt;x), F&lt;sup&gt;-&lt;/sup&gt; (x), with F&lt;sup&gt;-&lt;/sup&gt; (x) â‰¤ F&lt;sup&gt;+&lt;/sup&gt; (x), for all x in I, where F&lt;sup&gt;-&lt;/sup&gt; is lower semicontinuous and F&lt;sup&gt;+&lt;/sup&gt; is upper semicontinuous.</p>
